-- Spain Defeats Uruguay 2-1 to Open Confederations Cup Campaign
-- B y   T a r i q   P a n j a
-- 2013-06-16T23:56:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-06-16/spain-defeats-uruguay-2-1-to-open-confederations-cup-campaign.html
World champion Spain beat Uruguay
2-1 in its opening game at soccer’s Confederations Cup.  Pedro Rodriguez opened the scoring with a deflected shot in
the 20th minute in Recife,  Brazil , before Roberto Soldado added
Spain’s second 12 minutes later. Luis Suarez got Uruguay’s goal
with an 88th-minute free kick.  Nigeria and Tahiti, the other teams in Group B, meet in
Belo Horizonte tomorrow to complete the opening round of matches
at the eight-team tournament. Italy beat Mexico 2-1 today to
join Brazil on three points atop Group A. The tournament host
defeated Japan 3-0 in yesterday’s competition opener.  The Confederations Cup is a warm-up event for next year’s
World Cup in Brazil. The final is scheduled for June 30.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Tariq Panja in Rio de Janeiro at 
 tpanja@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
